Akanksha Jain:-Leave and licence agreement can be registered it has legal bindings and its clauses can be used legally if it is notarized or registered.the only diff. in leave and licence agreement is that it gives you(akanksha jain)  the power to leave the property with a prior notice of 2 or 3 months  as agreed on the document.For eg if you have taken it for a year you can leave that property with a prior notice after 4 months only.but you cant do this in 11 months clause.go for the police complain it can used as legal document after-all she has agreed not to take the electricity bill and she has signed the document.You can show her document that she agreed not to take electricity bill.  take you whole deposit dont even pay a penny and lodge a FIR.

Trust the Leave and License Agreement is a registered document wherein u have paid the proper stamp duty n registration fees. Since there is an inbuilt clause for obligation for payment of electricity bill on the landlord..so u can send him a legal notice..in case she does not respond to the legal notice then one can get d best compensation from the court...but that's time consuming...she has a right to terminate the agreement but u can take a stay order on the same from the court...basically getting into a legal battle will be a bit painful for u but yes it will be more painful for the landlord..n he will learn a lesson...secondly, it can get u the right compensation...
